Understanding the basics git work flow , staging changes , commiting them with messages , ignoring unwanted files, and viewing project history.


git status - this command helping what are the files are tracked and untracked .
git add    - this command can copy or cached you files from work repo staging area 

==> By default , after git install on your local pc have Master Branch

git branch -M main - This command helps you Move Master Branch to main 

git commit -m "this is day02 on 19June2025" --- this command help move the file from staging area to LocalRepo 

git log --oneline --- this command helps you to see the log in single line 

git ignore --- which ever the files i want skip to commit and push 

git push 